e the authors argue that the gender-equality mantra in Sweden has led to a society with increased opportunities for some, they also assert that the dominant norm of gender equality has become nationalistic and builds upon heteronormative and racial principles. Examining the changing meanings and parameters of gender equality against the country's social-democratic tradition and in the light of contemporary neoliberal ideologies, the book constitutes an urgent contribution to the debates about gender-equality policies and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 70(DE-601)1046171870(DE-588)4002805-7aArbeitswelt2gnd 70(DE-601)1063149550(DE-588)4021216-6aGleichberechtigung2gnd 70(DE-601)5013833790(DE-588)4845903-3aGender Mainstreaming2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aFahlgren, Siv, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiritli Nygren, Katarina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGriffin, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Gabriele, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohansson, Anders, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandén, Angelika Sjöstedt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLykke, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartinsson, Lena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartinsson, Lena, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMulinari, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNygren, Katarina Giritli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlofsdotter, Gunilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidegr